by localheinz at 2016-11-20T18:34:45Z

@keradus

The methods `setupBeforeClass()` and `tearDownAfterClass()` also have `public` visibility on the parent class, see

* [`PHPUnit_Framework_TestCase::setupBeforeClass()`](https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/blob/5.6/src/Framework/TestCase.php#L2249-L2256)
* [`PHPUnit_Framework_TestCase::tearDownAfterClass()`](https://github.com/sebastianbergmann/phpunit/blob/5.6/src/Framework/TestCase.php#L2298-L2305)

The other examples are from test case code examples, and there's no clear relation to the code examples extending `PHPUnit_Framework_TestCase` - shall I change them anyway?

